Exercise: Check if Two 3Ã—3Ã—3 Arrays Are Identical

Objective:
Write a function that checks whether two three-dimensional arrays have the same contents.

Instructions

Define two 3Ã—3Ã—3 arrays, m1 and m2.

Write a function equals that returns true if the arrays are identical, false otherwise.

Prompt the user to enter values for both arrays.

Display whether the arrays are identical.

Function Header
const int SIZE1 = 3, SIZE2 = 3, SIZE3 = 3;
bool equals(const int m1[SIZE1][SIZE2][SIZE3], const int m2[SIZE1][SIZE2][SIZE3]);

Example 1

Input:

Enter m1: 51 25 22 6 1 4 24 54 6
12 18 20 5 2 7 30 40 9
15 25 35 8 3 6 20 30 10

Enter m2: 51 25 22 6 1 4 24 54 6
12 18 20 5 2 7 30 40 9
15 25 35 8 3 6 20 30 10


Output:

Two arrays are identical.

Example 2

Input:

Enter m1: 51 25 22 6 1 4 24 54 6
12 18 20 5 2 7 30 40 9
15 25 35 8 3 6 20 30 10

Enter m2: 51 22 25 6 1 4 24 54 6
12 18 20 5 2 7 30 40 9
15 25 35 8 3 6 20 30 10


Output:

Two arrays are not identical.

C++ Solution
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

const int SIZE1 = 3, SIZE2 = 3, SIZE3 = 3;

// Function to check if two 3D arrays are identical
bool equals(const int m1[SIZE1][SIZE2][SIZE3], const int m2[SIZE1][SIZE2][SIZE3]) {
    for (int i = 0; i < SIZE1; i++)
        for (int j = 0; j < SIZE2; j++)
            for (int k = 0; k < SIZE3; k++)
                if (m1[i][j][k] != m2[i][j][k])
                    return false;
    return true;
}

int main() {
    int m1[SIZE1][SIZE2][SIZE3], m2[SIZE1][SIZE2][SIZE3];

    cout << "Enter elements for Matrix m1 (3x3x3):" << endl;
    for (int i = 0; i < SIZE1; i++)
        for (int j = 0; j < SIZE2; j++)
            for (int k = 0; k < SIZE3; k++)
                cin >> m1[i][j][k];

    cout << "Enter elements for Matrix m2 (3x3x3):" << endl;
    for (int i = 0; i < SIZE1; i++)
        for (int j = 0; j < SIZE2; j++)
            for (int k = 0; k < SIZE3; k++)
                cin >> m2[i][j][k];

    if (equals(m1, m2))
        cout << "Two arrays are identical." << endl;
    else
        cout << "Two arrays are not identical." << endl;

    return 0;
}

How It Works

equals function:

Loops through all elements in m1 and m2.

Returns false if any pair of elements differs.

Returns true if all elements match.

Main function:

Prompts the user to enter both arrays.

Calls equals to check for identity.

Displays the result.

